   <tbody> 
    <tr> 
     <th style="text-align: center;" colspan="2"> <h2>Stars of Ruin</h2> </th> 
    </tr> 
    <tr> 
     <td style="text-align: center;" colspan="2"><img title="Stars of Ruin" src="/file/Elden-Ring/stars_of_ruin_sorcery_elden_ring_wiki_guide_200px.png" alt="stars of ruin sorcery elden ring wiki guide 200px" width="200" height="200"></td> 
    </tr> 
    <tr> 
     <td>Spell Type</td> 
     <td><a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Primeval Sorceries" href="/Primeval+Sorceries" target="">Primeval Sorceries</a></td> 
    </tr> 
    <tr> 
     <td>FP Cost 32</td> 
     <td>Slots Used&nbsp;1</td> 
    </tr> 
    <tr> 
     <td colspan="2"><img title="item_effect_icon_elden_ring_wiki_guide_18px" src="/file/Elden-Ring/item_effects_icon_elden_ring_wiki_guide_55px_18px.png" alt="item effects icon elden ring wiki guide 55px 18px" width="18" height="18">Effect 
      <div class="lineleft">
        Fire twelve dark shooting stars that pursue foes 
      </div> <br><img style="float: left;" title="Attributes Requirement" src="/file/Elden-Ring/attributes-required-elden-ring-wiki-guide-18.png" alt="attributes required elden ring wiki guide 18" width="18" height="18">Requires 
      <div class="lineleft"> 
       <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Intelligence" href="/Intelligence" target="">Intelligence</a>&nbsp;43 
       <br> 
       <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Faith" href="/Faith" target="">Faith</a> 0 
       <br> 
       <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Arcane" href="/Arcane" target="">Arcane</a>&nbsp;0 
      </div> </td> 
    </tr> 
   </tbody> 
  </table> 
 </div> 
</div> 
<p><strong>Stars of Ruin</strong> is a&nbsp;<a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Sorceries" href="/Sorceries" target="">Sorcery</a> in <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Wiki" href="/Elden+Ring+Wiki">Elden Ring</a>. <strong>Stars of Ruin spell</strong>&nbsp;is a homing projectile spell that targets nearby foes and deals damage.&nbsp;Updated to&nbsp;<a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Patch Notes" href="/Patch+Notes">Patch 1.07</a>.</p> 
<p>&nbsp;</p> 
<div class="lineleft"> 
 <p><em>Legendary sorcery devised by Lusat, primeval sorcerers.&nbsp;</em></p> 
 <p><em>Fires twelve dark shooting stars that pursue the target. This sorcery can be cast while in motion. Charging increases potency.</em></p> 
 <p><em>When Lusat glimpsed into the primeval current, he beheld the final moments of a great star cluster, and upon seeing it, he too was broken.&nbsp;</em></p> 
</div> 
<p>&nbsp;</p> 
<h3 class="bonfire">Where to find Stars of Ruin</h3> 
<p>Where to find <strong>Stars of Ruin</strong>:</p> 
<ul> 
 <li><a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Caelid" href="/Caelid" target="">Caelid</a>: Given by <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Master Lusat" href="/Master+Lusat">Master Lusat</a> when interacted with inside the <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Sellia Hideaway" href="/Sellia+Hideaway">Sellia Hideaway</a>&nbsp;behind an arcane ward in the second pit. Requires the&nbsp;<strong>Sellian Sealbreaker </strong>to get through arcane ward (Acquired during <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Sorceress Sellen" href="/Sorceress+Sellen">Sorceress Sellen Questline</a>). <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Interactive Map?id=4478&amp;lat=-174.25&amp;lng=153.52&amp;zoom=8&amp;code=mapA" href="/Interactive+Map?id=4478&amp;lat=-174.25&amp;lng=153.52&amp;zoom=8&amp;code=mapA">Elden Ring Map Link</a></li> 
</ul> 
<p>&nbsp;</p> 
<h3 class="bonfire">Elden Ring&nbsp;Stars of Ruin Guide</h3> 
<ul> 
 <li><a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Primeval Sorceries" href="/Primeval+Sorceries">Primeval Sorcery</a></li> 
 <li>Since <strong>Patch 1.06</strong>, The target tracking ability of <strong>Stars of Ruin</strong> has been decreased.</li> 
 <li><span style="color: #ff9900;">Note:</span>&nbsp;In&nbsp;<a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Patch Notes" href="/Patch+Notes">Patch 1.07</a>, FP Cost has been reduced from 38 to 32, as well as Stamina Cost from 33 to 29.</li> 
 <li>Stamina Cost:&nbsp;29</li> 
 <li>Deals magic damage</li> 
 <li>This sorcery can be charged for extra damage at the cost of longer cast time.</li> 
 <li>Damage can be boosted by 15% by wearing <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Lusat's Glintstone Crown" href="/Lusat's+Glintstone+Crown">Lusat's Glintstone Crown</a>. This comes at the cost of a 15% increase in ALL sorcery costs</li> 
 <li>Due to the high number of projectiles, this spell can cause a lot of damage to a target's poise.&nbsp;</li> 
 <li>High FP cost can make it difficult to justify using for low level characters. For pure damage, other sorceries may be more efficient but the high tracking, high poise damage, decent range, and relatively good magic damage of this sorcery shouldn't be underestimated for those that are able to pay the price.</li> 
 <li>This sorcery becomes much more viable as a PvP sorcery if the character has the FP to use it regularly.&nbsp; 
  <ul> 
   <li>Repeated testing shows that it is not possible to fully dodge this sorcery with a standard roll. A target will take some damage as its projectiles hit one after another and will hit between i-frames.&nbsp;</li> 
   <li>This also makes this spell useful against faster-enemies that tend to dodge normal spells</li> 
  </ul> </li> 
 <li>The range of this spell is significantly lower than&nbsp;<a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Star Shower" href="/Star+Shower">Star Shower</a>&nbsp;or <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Glintstone Stars" href="/Glintstone+Stars">Glintstone Stars</a>.</li> 
</ul> 
<p>&nbsp;</p> 
