				<li id="16767473" class="cmnt-root" data="14" data-d="1662173364000"><ul class="comments"><li class="comment-box"><div class="avatar"><img src="/images/avatar.png" alt="" /><div class="comment-username">Anonymous</div></div><div class="comment"><div class="title"><span class="txt-subject"></span><input style="display: none;" class="txt-subject-ed"><span class="right cmt-ui"><a href="https://fextralife.com/forums/t579633/Stars-of-Ruin" rel="nofollow" target="_blank">02 Sep 2022 22:49</a>&nbsp;&nbsp;<a class="report-post" href="https://fextralife.com/forums/report.php?f=193&p=16767473" rel="nofollow" target="_blank" title="report this post"><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-flag" aria-hidden="true"></span></a></span></div><p class="txt-comment">After many PVP matches and invasions, can confirm that the latest patch nerfed this badly. It is way easier to dodge and is now easily outclassed by Star Shower for PVP purposes. Still works decently in PVE but I would still recommend Star Shower for a couple of reasons. <br/><br/>1. Stars of Ruin has less range and inferior tracking, yet it costs 65% more FP to cast. It does more damage but the tradeoff doesn&apos;t seem worth it, especially since the nerf.<br/><br/>2, Star Shower is superior in PVP. Not only does it have longer range but the stars move quicker when closing in on the target and the tracking is amazing. You will land far more consistently against opponents vs Stars of Ruin.<br/><br/>Overall, with a good amount of INT and a proper setup, Star Shower is just a generally better workhorse spell due to superior damage to FP ratio, better range and tracking and far better utility in PVP situations. </p><textarea style="display: none;" class="txt-comment-ed"></textarea><div class="clearfix"><a role="button" data-toggle="collapse" href="#zz-16767473" class="cmt-reply pull-right" href=""><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-share-alt"></span>Reply</a><a id="btnExpandComment" role="button" data-toggle="collapse" href="#re